name: Buckler
description: A common round shield. Lightweight and practical.

name: Chevalier Shield
description: A shield tailored for chevaliers. It's able to resist frontal lunge attacks.

name: Grand Shield
description: A huge shield that can cover its user's entire body.

name: Shield of Giants
description: A shield used by the ancient Giants. Its size is beyond human imagination.

name: Shield of Isaiah
description: A shield given by the prophet to his people. It can provide shelter to sincere followers.

name: Shield of Glory
description: A shield awarded to the veteran warrior in Veronica, the Holy Empire. It represents supreme glory.

name: Shield of Fairies
description: A shield blessed by fairies. It has incredible power.

name: Shield of the Chromatic Dragon
description: A shield crystal clear as jade. Said to be made of the scales of the ancient Chromatic Dragon. It can absorb all kinds of magic damage.

name: Sirius, Shield of Defending
description: A shield used in the War of Protectors. Represents law and order. It can absorb all kinds of magic damage.

name: Bronze Hammer
description: A common bronze hammer. Easy to wield.

name: Iron Hammer
description: A hammer made in batch by the blacksmith. It wields certain lethal power.

name: Hammer of Fortification
description: A sledgehammer used in the construction of a city. Those who are confident in their wrist strength can try to wield it.

name: Hammer of Giants
description: A hammer commonly used by the warriors of Giants. It is a symbol of strength.

name: Bonecrunching Hammer
description: A sledgehammer forged by a famous craftsman. It can crush the sturdiest of bones.

name: Hammer of Judgment
description: A hammer used by the Underworld Judge. Any soul trembles at the mere sight of it.

name: Earthshaker
description: A weapon used by Abadon, the founder of the Kingdom of Belgica. The earth shakes with its strikes.

name: Last Resort
description: A giant hammer used by Athenas, God of Destruction. It is capable of shattering the souls of living creatures.

name: Golbnus, Hammer of Chaos
description: A hammer used by the fallen Valkyrie in the Battle of the Polar Night. It is cursed with the spell of Hades, conjuring endless calamities.

name: Short Sword
description: A short and protective sword that even a child can use.

name: Great Sword
description: A big sword popular among mercenaries for flexing their strength.

name: Iron Sword
description: A very sharp sword meticulously forged by artisans.

name: Silver Sword
description: A sharp sword made of a rare metal.

name: Champion's Sword
description: A sword that can only be wielded by the valiant.

name: Electrum Sword
description: A sword forged from the sacred electrum by the eastern Ithacans. It has the power to purge evil.

name: Audhulma, the Lightborne
description: A sword made of jade from the frigid lands of Snegurochka. The swing of its blade envelopes all in frost.

name: Oath of Tirnanog
description: A sword gathering all the power of the Valkyrie Springwind. It successfully sealed the Dimension Demon in Lake Tirnanog.

name: Fensalir
description: A sword of soul enshrined in the Misery Palace that carries the resentment of Sepharad, the Protector of Souls. It's said to contain the power to kill any gods.

name: Hand Axe
description: A light and one-handed axe.

name: Mercenary Axe
description: A deadly axe commonly used by mercenaries.

name: Savage Axe
description: An axe popular among the barbarian warriors. Looks fearsome in hand.

name: Troll Axe
description: An axe used by trolls. It has a simple and crude shape.

name: Battle-tested Axe
description: A timeworn axe used by veteran warriors.

name: Soul-forging Axe
description: A legendary axe filled with its forger's soul.

name: Elf Axe
description: An axe that sank into the Elf Lake and absorbed the essence of the Forest of Elves.

name: Axe of the Primary Stone
description: A giant axe held by the God of Thunder. Able to sever any soul that is tied to this earthly realm.

name: Fredo, the Purgatory Axe
description: A manifestation of Fredo, the Purgatory Dragon. It can call upon the inferno that burns all enemies.

name: Dagger
description: A small short blade that can be hidden in one's sleeve.

name: Assassin Spike
description: A dagger fit for assassination.

name: Poisonous Dagger
description: A lethal dagger coated with poison.

name: Dagger of Temptation
description: A dagger used by an assassin in the guise of a dancer.

name: Stealth Dagger
description: A shining dagger that even glistens at night.

name: Soul Hunting Dagger
description: A cursed dagger that thirsts for souls.

name: Obsidian Dagger
description: A treasure handed down by generations of Dragonoids. It contains the mysterious power of the ancient dragon gods.

name: Blade of the Darkest Night
description: A dagger that can find its target even in the dark by using the Curse of Blood. It can awaken the user's instincts for assassination.

name: Ledear, Blade of the Underworld
description: A dagger used by the Protector of the Underworld. It's enshrined in the Misery Palace, capable of taking the lives of all intruders.

name: Wooden Bow
description: A crudely-made wooden bow that deals little damage.

name: Hunter Bow
description: A long hunting bow. Essential for any good hunter.

name: Crossbow
description: A bow that can fire arrows to hit a target at a great distance.

name: Ebony Bow
description: A highly durable bow made of ebony.

name: Platinum Bow
description: A precious bow that only aristocrats are permitted to use. Beautifully decorated.

name: Dragon Bow
description: A huge bow used to take down a dragon by the epic hero Hoperus.

name: Astral Bow
description: A magical bow that gathers the blessings of starlight.

name: Enuma Elish
description: An otherworldly bow summoned via evil alchemy. It is said it can destroy an entire city with a single shot.

name: Eurytus, the Godsend
description: A legendary bow held by the Goddess of the Moon, who once shot down the sun out of her anger against it.

name: Fragment
description: A book with many incomplete pages. Slightly difficult to read.

name: Apprentice Tome
description: A book that records spells for apprentices to learn.

name: Grimoire
description: A book that records commonly used spells, popular among sorcerers.

name: Tome of Storm
description: A precious book that records advanced spells.

name: Tome of Illusion
description: A book passed down by the sorcerer who claimed to be the most powerful in the world.

name: Night Owl Cursed Book
description: A book with detailed records of various forms of conjuring.

name: Codex of Prophecy
description: A sacred book passed down through generations in the Ithacan prophets of the east.

name: Chronospace Breach
description: A grimoire that records the highest level of dimensional magic. It is said to be left by the Chronospace Goddess of the Primeval Time.

name: Ivaldi
description: A book of the supreme code that bestows infinite wisdom and magic upon its owner.

name: Harp
description: An ordinary harp.

name: Musician's Harp
description: A harp favored by musicians. It can produce simple music.

name: Bard's Harp
description: A harp often used by bards to play elegant, emotional melodies.

name: Lyre of Lament
description: A harp handed down to future generations by a frustrated musician. It seems to speak of its former owner's grief.

name: Melody of Elysium
description: A magical instrument used by Forest Fairies to bring happiness.

name: Notes of Temptation
description: An instrument used by sirens to seduce crews.

name: Song of the Damned
description: An instrument that praises the war exploits of the Demon soldiers. It is capable of playing the sounds of Devildom.

name: Ballad of Death
description: An instrument enshrined in the Misery Palace. It can play a melody that manipulates the souls of creatures to fall into the abyss of the Underworld.

name: Warsong of Inanna
description: An artifact held by the Valkyrie, Inanna. It stimulates the potential of creatures to unlock their soul power.

name: Dim Orb
description: An orb that emits no luster.

name: Spiritual Orb
description: An orb used to gather spiritual power during the séance ceremony.

name: Crystal Orb
description: A transparent orb that contains incredible magic.

name: Demon Sealing Orb
description: An ominous orb that sealed a demon.

name: Orb of Oracle
description: A miraculous orb. It's believed among its followers to be able to hear the oracles.

name: Shimmering Star
description: A gorgeous and mysterious orb.

name: Solar Orb
description: A treasure passed down through generations in the ancestral tribes of the Sunfaith World. It has an emblem of the sun.

name: Clotho's Choice
description: A magical orb containing the power of the Auguring Star. It can reveal the future.

name: Uluru's Eye, the Primeval
description: An item containing the power of Uluru's Eye, the Primeval Dragon. It can lead to a future of infinite possibilities.

name: Glass Grail
description: An ordinary grail made of glass.

name: Spiritual Grail
description: A grail used to store spiritual power which can be unleashed in combat.

name: Amethyst Grail
description: A grail carefully crafted from amethyst. It can resonate with the magic inside the user's body.

name: Exorcising Grail
description: A grail with the power to purify evil.

name: Healing Grail
description: A grail that holds the healing power of hierophants.

name: Elf Grail
description: A grail filled with the water from Elf Lake, more or less blessed by the elves.

name: Dragon Blood Grail
description: A cursed grail containing the blood of an evil dragon.

name: Seraph Grail
description: A magical grail that converts the holder's spiritual power into vigor. It can heal any injury as long as power is supplied.

name: Mihr, the Grail of Life
description: An artifact that is used by the goddess Mihr to endow all creatures with the power of resurrection. It's regarded as the origin of life.

name: Wooden Staff
description: An ordinary staff with nothing special.

name: Prophecy Staff
description: A staff that can foretell certain signs.

name: Priest Staff
description: A staff that priests use to gather their mana.

name: Thunder Staff
description: A staff that evokes lightning and thunder.

name: Staff of Great Eye
description: An evil staff with a great eye carved on it.

name: Dawn's Blessing
description: A magical staff that gathers the power of the Morning Star.

name: Forbidden Staff
description: A malevolent staff wielded by the King of Gaheris only in the rituals of demonic descent.

name: Scepter of the High Seat
description: A staff symbolic of Veronica, the Holy Empire. It's said to be the holy staff used by the White Empress to pacify the chaos.

name: Ashkelon
description: A sacred staff used in the Battle of Ashkelon. Said to be a symbol of the Sun God.

name: Dysoxylum Wand
description: A common wand used for magic chanting.

name: Psychic Wand
description: A wand for chanting physical spells.

name: Summoner's Wand
description: A precious wand used in summoning rituals.

name: Ruby Wand
description: A wand decorated with a carnelian.

name: Syphon Wand
description: A magic wand that chants soul-consuming magic.

name: Dragon Fang
description: A wand made of dragon fangs.

name: Calamity of Fallen Gods
description: A wand that summoned the half-man monster Draupnir during the Battle of Nayd.

name: Uroboros
description: A wand that sank into Lake Aphroca of the Underworld. It can unleash the uroboros power of its user.

name: Gygeurs, Sanction of Divinity
description: A staff of trials passed down in the Underworld. It is used to judge whether the souls of the dead may enter hell.

name: Leather Armor
description: A piece of leather armor that is easy to wear.

name: A Piece of Armor
description: A common piece of armor offering some protection.

name: Hauberk
description: A piece of armor made of iron wire offering a good defense.

name: Paladin's Armor
description: A piece of armor popular among chevaliers, rigid and durable.

name: Ebony Armor
description: A piece of intimidating armor that's thoroughly painted black.

name: Champion's Armor
description: A piece of armor only for those battle-hardened heroes.

name: Dragon-emblazoned Armor
description: A piece of armor with a dragon pattern on it. Said to be worn by the dragon slayer.

name: Armor of the Underworld
description: A piece of armor worn by the Demon soldiers from the Underworld. It emits an intimidating hellish aura.

name: Helius, the Supreme
description: A supreme masterpiece forged from the bones of the demigod Badoras by the elven artisan Kordaregan in the Primeval Time, as a homage to this deceased hero.

name: Cloth Outfit
description: An ordinary garment made of cloth.

name: Corset
description: A skintight garment.

name: Prayer's Gown
description: A robe worn only at prayer services, plain but still with grace.

name: Padre's Cassock
description: A daily robe worn by the priests of the Holy Church.

name: Nevers Robe
description: A vestment worn by the bishops at the advent ceremony. Light and ethereal.

name: Cape of the Archmagus
description: An awe-inspiring cloak worn by the Archmagus.

name: Dragon's Blood Gown
description: A gown worn by the Queen of the Dragon Empire on the Island of Padora.

name: Robe of Stardust
description: A garment gathering the aura of stars. Airy, elegant, and pliant.

name: Proiades, Vestment of Polar Night
description: A holy cloak worn by the Protector who controls the Intangible. No ordinary person can come near it, and its emanation of power can easily melt enemies' weapons.

name: Ring
description: An ordinary ring commonly sold at stores.

name: Stinger
description: A ring favored by assassins. Said to be of magical protection.

name: Amethyst Ring
description: A ring with purple jade inlay. It must command an extraordinary price.

name: Alluvial Gold Ring
description: A ring made of fine grains of gold.

name: Dark Chevalier Ring
description: A symbol of the Dark Chivalric Order of Farias. It's seen by the chevaliers as their pride.

name: Enchanted Ring
description: A legendary magic ring that robs the wearers of their sanity.

name: Moonlight Ring
description: A magic ring that absorbs the essence of the moonlight. The pattern of the starry sky faintly appears on it.

name: Ring of Draupnir
description: A ring worn by the half-man monster Draupnir during the Battle of Nayd. It constantly devours its wearer's soul and converts it into endless magic power.

name: Andvari, Ring of Genesis
description: A sacred object congealed from the eternal snow on the Creation Apex. Pure white and immaculate. Its wearer can go anywhere without restraint.

name: Necklace
description: An ordinary necklace sold in markets.

name: Enchanted Necklace
description: A necklace with some magic power.

name: Silver Necklace
description: A silver necklace that accentuates the gentility of its wearer.

name: Coral Necklace
description: A necklace crafted from coral, popular in the Southern Islands.

name: Spirit Necklace
description: A magical necklace used to host the souls of the deceased during the advent ceremony.

name: Demonsbane Necklace
description: A magic necklace favored among magicians in the far east. It is said to be able to cleanse evil and champion justice.

name: Dark Necklace
description: An accessory worn by General Axe Van Pelos who is a guard of Purgatory. It can summon the flames of purgatory.

name: Collar of Alice
description: A magical accessory. Said to be worn by the maiden who guards the Sacred Tree.

name: Brisingamen, the Sacred
description: A sacred object dedicated to the Supreme God to eulogize the God's act of creating the world.

name: Hammer of the Wild
description: A weapon crafted from a large piece of beast bone. Contains the strength of the wild.

name: Axe of the Wild
description: A weapon crafted from a large piece of beast bone. Contains the strength of the wild.

name: Dagger of the Wild
description: A weapon crafted from a large piece of beast bone. Contains the strength of the wild.

name: Tome of the Wild
description: A weapon crafted from a large piece of beast bone. Contains the strength of the wild.

name: Orb of the Wild
description: A weapon crafted from a large piece of beast bone. Contains the strength of the wild.

name: Wand of the Wild
description: A weapon crafted from a large piece of beast bone. Contains the strength of the wild.

name: Garment of the Wild
description: A garment crafted from a large piece of beast bone. Contains the strength of the wild.

name: Ring of the Wild
description: An accessory crafted from a large piece of beast bone. Contains the strength of the wild.

name: Shield of Thorns
description: The front of the shield is covered in magical vines and thorns, making those who approach recklessly backfired by magic.

name: Sword of Thorns
description: The hilt of the sword is covered in magical vines and thorns, making those who approach recklessly backfired by magic.

name: Bow of Thorns
description: The bow is covered in magical vines and thorns, making those who approach recklessly backfired by magic.

name: Lyre of Thorns
description: The instrument is covered in magical vines and thorns, making those who approach recklessly backfired by magic.

name: Grail of Thorns
description: The grail is covered in magical vines and thorns, making those who approach recklessly backfired by magic.

name: Staff of Thorns
description: The staff is covered in magical vines and thorns, making those who approach recklessly backfired by magic.

name: Garment of Thorns
description: The garment is covered in magical vines and thorns, making those who approach recklessly backfired by magic.

name: Ring of Thorns
description: The ring is covered in magical vines and thorns, making those who approach recklessly backfired by magic.

name: Shield of the Earth
description: A shield infused with the essence of the earth and possesses great physical resistance.

name: Sword of the Earth
description: A sword infused with the essence of the earth and possesses great physical resistance.

name: Bow of the Earth
description: A bow infused with the essence of the earth and possesses great physical resistance.

name: Lyre of the Earth
description: An instrument infused with the essence of the earth and possesses great physical resistance.

name: Grail of the Earth
description: A grail infused with the essence of the earth and possesses great physical resistance.

name: Staff of the Earth
description: A staff infused with the essence of the earth and possesses great physical resistance.

name: Armor of the Earth
description: A piece of armor infused with the essence of the earth and possesses great physical resistance.

name: Necklace of the Earth
description: A necklace infused with the essence of the earth and possesses great physical resistance.

name: Hammer of Still Water
description: A weapon blessed by the Goddess of the Lake, and able to resist the corrosion of magic.

name: Axe of Still Water
description: A weapon blessed by the Goddess of the Lake, and able to resist the corrosion of magic.

name: Dagger of Still Water
description: A weapon blessed by the Goddess of the Lake, and able to resist the corrosion of magic.

name: Tome of Still Water
description: A tome blessed by the Goddess of the Lake, and able to resist the corrosion of magic.

name: Orb of Still Water
description: An orb blessed by the Goddess of the Lake, and able to resist the corrosion of magic.

name: Wand of Still Water
description: A wand blessed by the Goddess of the Lake, and able to resist the corrosion of magic.

name: Armor of Still Water
description: A piece of armor blessed by the Goddess of the Lake, and able to resist the corrosion of magic.

name: Necklace of Still Water
description: A necklace blessed by the Goddess of the Lake, and able to resist the corrosion of magic.

name: Xmas Tree Sword
description: A sword shaped like a Christmas tree, often mistaken for an ordinary ornament.

name: Xmas Bell
description: A bell-alike weapon, tinkling merrily and gently.
